<i>adjective</i>: 죄송하다 [죄ː송하다/줴ː송하다], 죄송스럽다 [죄ː송스럽따/줴ː송스럽따], 안되다 [안되다/안뒈다], 송구하다 [송ː구하다], 송구스럽다 [송ː구스럽따], 섭섭하다 [섭써파다], 서운하다 [서운하다], 미안하다 [미안하다] <i>interjection</i>: 어 [어], 네 [네] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>adjective</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>죄송하다 [죄ː송하다/줴ː송하다]</dt><br>
<dd>sorry</dd><br>
<dd>죄를 지은 것처럼 몹시 미안하다.</dd><br>
<dd>Very sorry as if one committed a wrongdoing.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>죄송스럽다 [죄ː송스럽따/줴ː송스럽따]</dt><br>
<dd>sorry</dd><br>
<dd>죄를 지은 것처럼 미안한 마음이 들다.</dd><br>
<dd>Feeling sorry as if one committed a wrongdoing.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>안되다 [안되다/안뒈다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. pitiful; poor; sorry</dd><br>
<dd>불쌍하고 가엾어서 마음이 좋지 않다.</dd><br>
<dd>Not feeling good about someone because he/she looks poor and pathetic.</dd><br>
<dd>2. gaunt; haggard</dd><br>
<dd>근심이나 병 등으로 얼굴이 많이 상하다.</dd><br>
<dd>Looking stricken with a disease, worry, etc.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>송구하다 [송ː구하다]</dt><br>
<dd>sorry</dd><br>
<dd>몹시 미안하여 마음이 편하지 않다.</dd><br>
<dd>To feel uncomfortable because one feels sorry for something.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>송구스럽다 [송ː구스럽따]</dt><br>
<dd>sorry</dd><br>
<dd>몹시 미안하여 거북한 마음이 있다.</dd><br>
<dd>To feel uncomfortable because one feels sorry for something.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>섭섭하다 [섭써파다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. sorry; regrettable</dd><br>
<dd>서운하고 아쉽다.</dd><br>
<dd>Sorry and feeling the lack of someone or something.</dd><br>
<dd>2. sad</dd><br>
<dd>없어지는 것이 슬프고 아깝다.</dd><br>
<dd>Sad and sorry about someone or something disappearing.</dd><br>
<dd>3. disappointed</dd><br>
<dd>기대에 어긋나 서운하거나 불만스럽다.</dd><br>
<dd>Sorry and dissatisfied because something fails to meet one's expectations.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>서운하다 [서운하다]</dt><br>
<dd>sorry; remorseful</dd><br>
<dd>생각처럼 되지 않아 만족스럽지 못하다.</dd><br>
<dd>Not satisfied with something because it did not go according to one's expectation.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>미안하다 [미안하다]</dt><br>
<dd>1. regrettable; sorry</dd><br>
<dd>남에게 잘못을 하여 마음이 편치 못하고 부끄럽다.</dd><br>
<dd>Feeling rather uncomfortable and ashamed because one did something bad to someone.</dd><br>
<dd>2. I am sorry</dd><br>
<dd>겸손하게 양해를 구할 때 쓰는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>A word used to seek someone's pardon in a modest way.</dd><br>
</li>
<li><i>interjection</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>어 [어]</dt><br>
<dd>1. yes; yup; yeah</dd><br>
<dd>상대방의 부름에 대답할 때 쓰는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An exclamation used when answering the call of someone.</dd><br>
<dd>2. yes; yeah; okay</dd><br>
<dd>상대방의 물음이나 명령 등에 긍정하여 대답할 때 쓰는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An exclamation used when giving a positive answer to someone's question, order, etc.</dd><br>
<dd>3. what; sorry; beg your pardon</dd><br>
<dd>상대방의 말을 다시 물을 때 쓰는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An exclamation used when asking again what the other party said.</dd><br>
<dd>4. huh; eh</dd><br>
<dd>상대방에게 대답이나 행동을 빨리 하도록 조를 때 쓰는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An exclamation used when urging someone to answer or act quickly.</dd><br>
<dd>5. eh; huh</dd><br>
<dd>상대방의 말이나 행동이 마음에 들지 않아 불평을 할 때 쓰는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An exclamation used when the speaker makes a complaint because he/she does not like the other party's way of speaking or behaving.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>네 [네]</dt><br>
<dd>1. yes; yes sir; yes ma'am</dd><br>
<dd>윗사람의 부름에 대답할 때 쓰는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An exclamation uttered when the speaker answers the call of his/her elder.</dd><br>
<dd>2. yes; yes sir; yes ma'am</dd><br>
<dd>윗사람의 물음이나 명령 등에 긍정하여 대답할 때 쓰는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An exclamation uttered when the speaker affirmatively answers the call or order of his/her superior.</dd><br>
<dd>3. excuse me; sorry; I beg your pardon</dd><br>
<dd>윗사람의 말을 다시 물을 때 쓰는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An exclamation uttered when the speaker asks again what his/her superior said.</dd><br>
<dd>4. please</dd><br>
<dd>윗사람에게 무엇을 조를 때 쓰는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An exclamation uttered when the speaker pesters his/her elder for something.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>